definition.value: An N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl group obtained formally by removal of the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of di-(D-mannosylated) alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc. In the structure shown, either two of the R atoms each represent a D-mannopyranosyl group, or one of the R atoms reprsents a di-D-mannosyl group; all remaining R atoms = H.

An N-glycoprotein resulting from the formal condensation of the side-chain carboxamide group of the L-asparagine residues in the genome polyprotein of hepatitus C virus subtype 1a with the hemiacetal group of D-mannosylated alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc. It has been found at positions 417, 423, 448, 540, 556, and 623 of the protein (positions 35, 41, 66, 158, 174, and 241 in PMID:18187336, respectively). In the structure shown, either two of the R atoms each represent a D-mannopyranosyl group, or one of the R atoms reprsents a di-D-mannosyl group; all remaining R atoms = H.
A 2-hydroxy-6-oxo-2,4-heptadienoate which has 2Z,4E configuration. Obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of (2Z,4E)-2-hydroxy-6-oxohepta-2,4-dienoic acid, it is the major species at pH 7.3.
A deoxypentose that is alpha-D-ribofuranose in which the hydroxy group at position 5 is substituted by a hydrogen.

An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of 5-deoxy-alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of R- and S-mefentrifluconazole.  A fungicide developed by BASF for the control of Septoria in wheat.
The hydroxyl functionalities could be either on C2 and C4 positions of the aromatic ring (as in 2-hydroxy-p-coumaric acid) or on the C3 and C4 positions (as in caffeic acid).
A dihydroxycinnamic acid hexoside where the hexoside is linked to the aromatic ring via an ether or acetal bond.
A dihydroxycinnamic acid acetylhexoside where the acid group is esterified with an acetylhexose group.
A dihydroxycinnamic acid acetylhexoside with the presence of an additional carboxylic acid group
